transcript.text: Hello and welcome to On Print Shop.
In today's video, we're excited to introduce you to the Media Gallery management feature, a game changer for enhancing your designer, studio and website experience.
Imagine being able to guide your customers with engaging videos and images, simplifying their design journey, supporting purchases, or even showcasing your impressive portfolio.
This feature makes all that possible.
Ready to add some magic to your studio?
Navigate to the Content Management section and open the brand new Media Gallery menu.
Click on the Add button and decide whether to upload a video or image.
Let's unlock the possibilities for videos.
All it takes is a few clicks.
Select the stores where it will appear, add the URL of your chosen platform, upload an eye-catching thumbnail and categorize your media or create a fresh category on the fly using the plus icon.
Add a compelling title and decide where this media should shine in the Designer studio, on CMS pages, or both, and assign it to the product type.
To ensure everything looks seamless, set the display sequence using a sorting number, activate the status, and click Save and back.
Just like that, your media gallery begins to take shape.
You can even add GIFs for a dynamic touch.
You can also customize the tab's position with a simple sorting order adjustment.
The tutorial icon will be available in the bottom left corner, where users can effortlessly browse videos and images.
Categories make filtering easy, ensuring your customers find exactly what they need.
Videos are just a click away, while images are kept in their exclusive category.
It's a visual treat that simplifies the design process and elevates user experience.
And there you have it.
With the Media Gallery feature, you're not just assisting your customers, you're inspiring them.
Start creating and let your media do the talking.
We look forward to seeing how these updates help enhance your business operations.
If you have any questions, our support executives are here to help.
Just reach out through live chat on on printshop.com.
Thanks for tuning in.
